Johannesburg - Floods and heavy rains wreaked havoc in parts of Gauteng as severe weather continued. Authorities on Friday warned motorists to be cautious as many low-lying bridges had become flooded. Several rivers in Gauteng reached extremelyÂ high levels. The Hennops River in Centurion and the Apies River have broken its banks due to excessive flooding and the Jukskei River remains at a dangerous level, authorities said. The flooding has affected electricity supply as power outages have been reported in Johannesburg's northern suburbs. There have also been numerous reports of fallen trees at Melrose and Fourways and there is a sinkhole on the road leading to Valhalla from the R55. Read more: PICS AND VIDEOS: Traffic chaos expected as flash floods hit Joburg                     IOL